defs.docs: Core primitives for `tokio-trace`.

defs.name: callsite
defs.docs:
Callsites represent the source locations from which spans or events
 originate.

defs.name: Callsite
defs.docs: Trait implemented by callsites.

defs.name: add_interest
defs.docs:
Adds the [`Interest`] returned by [registering] the callsite with a
 [dispatcher].

defs.name: clear_interest
defs.docs: Remove _all_ [`Interest`] from the callsite, disabling it.

defs.name: metadata
defs.docs: Returns the [metadata] associated with the callsite.

defs.name: Identifier
defs.docs: Uniquely identifies a [`Callsite`]

defs.name: register
defs.docs: Register a new `Callsite` with the global registry.

defs.name: dispatcher
defs.docs: Dispatches trace events to `Subscriber`s.

defs.name: Dispatch
defs.docs: `Dispatch` trace data to a [`Subscriber`].

defs.name: with_default
defs.value: fn <T> (dispatcher: &Dispatch, f: impl FnOnce() -> T) -> T
defs.docs: Sets this dispatch as the default for the duration of a closure.

defs.name: get_default
defs.docs: Executes a closure with a reference to this thread's current [dispatcher].

defs.name: none
defs.docs: Returns a new `Dispatch` that discards events and spans.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Returns a `Dispatch` that forwards to the given [`Subscriber`].

defs.name: register_callsite
defs.docs:
Registers a new callsite with this subscriber, returning whether or not
 the subscriber is interested in being notified about the callsite.

defs.name: new_span
defs.docs:
Record the construction of a new span, returning a new [ID] for the
 span being constructed.

defs.name: record
defs.docs: Record a set of values on a span.

defs.name: record_follows_from
defs.docs:
Adds an indication that `span` follows from the span with the id
 `follows`.

defs.name: enabled
defs.docs:
Returns true if a span with the specified [metadata] would be
 recorded.

defs.name: event
defs.docs: Records that an [`Event`] has occurred.

defs.name: enter
defs.docs: Records that a span has been entered.

defs.name: exit
defs.docs: Records that a span has been exited.

defs.name: clone_span
defs.docs: Notifies the subscriber that a [span ID] has been cloned.

defs.name: drop_span
defs.docs: Notifies the subscriber that a [span ID] has been dropped.

defs.name: event
defs.docs: Events represent single points in time during the execution of a program.

defs.name: Event
defs.docs:
`Event`s represent single points in time where something occurred during the
 execution of a program.

defs.name: dispatch
defs.docs:
Constructs a new `Event` with the specified metadata and set of values,
 and observes it with the current subscriber.

defs.name: record
defs.docs: Visits all the fields on this `Event` with the specified [visitor].

defs.name: fields
defs.docs: Returns an iterator over the set of values on this `Event`.

defs.name: metadata
defs.docs: Returns [metadata] describing this `Event`.

defs.name: field
defs.docs: Span and `Event` key-value data.

defs.name: Field
defs.docs:
An opaque key allowing _O_(1) access to a field in a `Span`'s key-value
 data.

defs.name: FieldSet
defs.docs: Describes the fields present on a span.

defs.name: names
defs.docs: The names of each field on the described span.

defs.name: callsite
defs.docs: The callsite where the described span originates.

defs.name: ValueSet
defs.docs: A set of fields and values for a span.

defs.name: Iter
defs.docs: An iterator over a set of fields.

defs.name: Visit
defs.docs: Visits typed values.

defs.name: record_i64
defs.docs: Visit a signed 64-bit integer value.

defs.name: record_u64
defs.docs: Visit an umsigned 64-bit integer value.

defs.name: record_bool
defs.docs: Visit a boolean value.

defs.name: record_str
defs.docs: Visit a string value.

defs.name: record_debug
defs.docs: Visit a value implementing `fmt::Debug`.

defs.name: Value
defs.docs: A field value of an erased type.

defs.name: record
defs.docs: Visits this value with the given `Visitor`.

defs.name: DisplayValue
defs.docs: A `Value` which serializes as a string using `fmt::Display`.

defs.name: DebugValue
defs.docs: A `Value` which serializes as a string using `fmt::Debug`.

defs.name: display
defs.docs:
Wraps a type implementing `fmt::Display` as a `Value` that can be
 recorded using its `Display` implementation.

defs.name: debug
defs.docs:
Wraps a type implementing `fmt::Debug` as a `Value` that can be
 recorded using its `Debug` implementation.

defs.name: callsite
defs.docs:
Returns an [`Identifier`] that uniquely identifies the [`Callsite`]
 which defines this field.

defs.name: name
defs.docs: Returns a string representing the name of the field.

defs.name: field
defs.docs: Returns the [`Field`] named `name`, or `None` if no such field exists.

defs.name: contains
defs.docs: Returns `true` if `self` contains the given `field`.

defs.name: iter
defs.docs: Returns an iterator over the `Field`s in this `FieldSet`.

defs.name: value_set
defs.value: fn <'v, V> (&'v self, values: &'v V) -> ValueSet<'v>
defs.docs: Returns a new `ValueSet` with entries for this `FieldSet`'s values.

defs.name: len
defs.docs: Returns the number of fields in this `FieldSet`.

defs.name: callsite
defs.docs:
Returns an [`Identifier`] that uniquely identifies the [`Callsite`]
 defining the fields this `ValueSet` refers to.

defs.name: ValidLen
defs.docs:
Marker trait implemented by arrays which are of valid length to
 construct a `ValueSet`.

defs.name: metadata
defs.docs: Metadata describing trace data.

defs.name: Metadata
defs.value: Metadata { name, target, level, module_path, file, line, fields }
defs.docs: Metadata describing a [span] or [event].

defs.name: name
defs.docs: The name of the span described by this metadata.

defs.name: target
defs.docs:
The part of the system that the span that this metadata describes
 occurred in.

defs.name: level
defs.docs: The level of verbosity of the described span.

defs.name: module_path
defs.docs:
The name of the Rust module where the span occurred, or `None` if this
 could not be determined.

defs.name: file
defs.docs:
The name of the source code file where the span occurred, or `None` if
 this could not be determined.

defs.name: line
defs.docs:
The line number in the source code file where the span occurred, or
 `None` if this could not be determined.

defs.name: fields
defs.docs:
The names of the key-value fields attached to the described span or
 event.

defs.name: Level
defs.docs: Describes the level of verbosity of a span or event.

defs.name: new
defs.value: fn (name: &'static str, target: &'a str, level: Level, module_path: Option<&'a str>, file: Option<&'a str>, line: Option<u32>, field_names: &'static [&'static str], callsite: &'static Callsite) -> Self
defs.docs:
Construct new metadata for a span, with a name, target, level, field
 names, and optional source code location.

defs.name: fields
defs.docs: Returns the set of fields on the described span.

defs.name: level
defs.docs: Returns the level of verbosity of the described span.

defs.name: name
defs.docs: Returns the name of the span.

defs.name: target
defs.docs:
Returns a string describing the part of the system where the span or
 event that this metadata describes occurred.

defs.name: module_path
defs.docs:
Returns the path to the Rust module where the span occurred, or
 `None` if the module path is unknown.

defs.name: file
defs.docs:
Returns the name of the source code file where the span
 occurred, or `None` if the file is unknown

defs.name: line
defs.docs:
Returns the line number in the source code file where the span
 occurred, or `None` if the line number is unknown.

defs.name: callsite
defs.docs:
Returns an opaque `Identifier` that uniquely identifies the callsite
 this `Metadata` originated from.

defs.name: ERROR
defs.docs: The "error" level.

defs.name: WARN
defs.docs: The "warn" level.

defs.name: INFO
defs.docs: The "info" level.

defs.name: DEBUG
defs.docs: The "debug" level.

defs.name: TRACE
defs.docs: The "trace" level.

defs.name: span
defs.docs: Spans represent periods of time in the execution of a program.

defs.name: Id
defs.docs: Identifies a span within the context of a subscriber.

defs.name: Attributes
defs.docs:
Attributes provided to a `Subscriber` describing a new span when it is
 created.

defs.name: Record
defs.docs: A set of fields recorded by a span.

defs.name: from_u64
defs.docs: Constructs a new span ID from the given `u64`.

defs.name: into_u64
defs.docs: Returns the span's ID as a  `u64`.

defs.name: new
defs.docs:
Returns `Attributes` describing a new child span of the current span,
 with the provided metadata and values.

defs.name: new_root
defs.docs:
Returns `Attributes` describing a new span at the root of its own trace
 tree, with the provided metadata and values.

defs.name: child_of
defs.value: fn (parent: Id, metadata: &'a Metadata<'a>, values: &'a field::ValueSet<'a>) -> Self
defs.docs:
Returns `Attributes` describing a new child span of the specified
 parent span, with the provided metadata and values.

defs.name: metadata
defs.docs: Returns a reference to the new span's metadata.

defs.name: values
defs.docs:
Returns a reference to a `ValueSet` containing any values the new span
 was created with.

defs.name: is_root
defs.docs: Returns true if the new span shoold be a root.

defs.name: is_contextual
defs.docs:
Returns true if the new span's parent should be determined based on the
 current context.

defs.name: parent
defs.docs: Returns the new span's explicitly-specified parent, if there is one.

defs.name: record
defs.docs:
Records all the fields in this set of `Attributes` with the provided
 [Visitor].

defs.name: contains
defs.docs:
Returns `true` if this set of `Attributes` contains a value for the
 given `Field`.

defs.name: is_empty
defs.docs: Returns true if this set of `Attributes` contains _no_ values.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Constructs a new `Record` from a `ValueSet`.

defs.name: record
defs.docs: Records all the fields in this `Record` with the provided [Visitor].

defs.name: contains
defs.docs: Returns `true` if this `Record` contains a value for the given `Field`.

defs.name: is_empty
defs.docs: Returns true if this `Record` contains _no_ values.

defs.name: subscriber
defs.docs: Subscribers collect and record trace data.

defs.name: Subscriber
defs.docs: Trait representing the functions required to collect trace data.

defs.name: register_callsite
defs.docs:
Registers a new callsite with this subscriber, returning whether or not
 the subscriber is interested in being notified about the callsite.

defs.name: enabled
defs.docs:
Returns true if a span or event with the specified [metadata] would be
 recorded.

defs.name: new_span
defs.docs:
Visit the construction of a new span, returning a new [span ID] for the
 span being constructed.

defs.name: record
defs.docs: Record a set of values on a span.

defs.name: record_follows_from
defs.docs:
Adds an indication that `span` follows from the span with the id
 `follows`.

defs.name: event
defs.docs: Records that an [`Event`] has occurred.

defs.name: enter
defs.docs: Records that a span has been entered.

defs.name: exit
defs.docs: Records that a span has been exited.

defs.name: clone_span
defs.docs: Notifies the subscriber that a [span ID] has been cloned.

defs.name: drop_span
defs.docs: Notifies the subscriber that a [span ID] has been dropped.

defs.name: Interest
defs.docs: Indicates a [`Subscriber`]'s interest in a particular callsite.

defs.name: never
defs.docs:
Returns an `Interest` indicating that the subscriber is never interested
 in being notified about a callsite.

defs.name: sometimes
defs.docs:
Returns an `Interest` indicating  the subscriber is sometimes interested
 in being notified about a callsite.

defs.name: always
defs.docs:
Returns an `Interest` indicating  the subscriber is always interested in
 being notified about a callsite.

defs.name: is_never
defs.docs:
Returns `true` if the subscriber is never interested in being notified
 about this callsite.

defs.name: is_sometimes
defs.docs:
Returns `true` if the subscriber is sometimes interested in being notified
 about this callsite.

defs.name: is_always
defs.docs:
Returns `true` if the subscriber is always interested in being notified
 about this callsite.
